---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Mission Briefing" subtitle="// Contract Terms — Read Before Signing">
  <h1 class="text-3xl text-neon-cyan glow-cyan mb-6">Mission Briefing</h1>

  <p class="text-fg-dim mb-8">
    Standard Registry contract. Non-standard target. Read the terms; show up prepared.
  </p>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-neon-amber uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Objective</h2>
    <p>Retrieve the Machiavelli mainframe access code. Extract cleanly. Do not engage security.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-neon-amber uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Team Composition</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">
      Operators will deploy in two-person crews, or a handful of small competing
      squads — Dispatch will call it on the night based on headcount. Expect your
      partner to be assigned, not chosen. The Registry doesn't indulge cliques.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each crew runs the op in parallel. You will not have line of sight on the
      others. Progress made by one crew does not carry to another; a code cracked
      in one room is a code you still have to crack yourselves. Coordinate within
      your crew, compete between them, and remember: the Registry pays on delivery,
      not on participation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-neon-amber uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Loadout</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-fg-dim">
      <li>A working phone or laptop (Registry toolkit access).</li>
      <li>Pen and paper. Cipher work is easier on paper than you think.</li>
      <li>Patience. This is not a brute-force op.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-neon-amber uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Logistics</h2>
    <p class="mb-3">
      Muster point, arrival window, and operation start time will be transmitted
      through secure channels as the date approaches. Do not share externally. Do
      not ask questions in the open. If the Registry wanted Machiavelli to know
      we were coming, we'd have sent a postcard.
    </p>
    <p>
      Arrive on time, and arrive dressed for the job. Think low-light streets and
      places you'd rather not be seen. Scavenged layers, dark tones, a little edge.
      Registry operators aren't corporate — don't look it.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
